comments.text: Meraki wireless Access Points will also create a remote tunnel to the cloud upon startup, they use an onboard VPN. Those APs will also scan the network looking for other devices on the network and will cache the network configuration locally on the device. @4:02 To describe it as a "tunnel building piece of malware" is alarmist and out of touch with reality. They are not hiding these capabilities on the dog, this is poorly designed and their API routing needs to be improved. This situation bears the hallmarks of an engineering team designing with performance in mind where security isn't an after thought, it's not considered whatsoever. This lack of due care was correctly called out by the security researchers. The company needs to implement security controls yes but that's not the same as malicious intent, this is "wanton disregard". If there was intentional malfeasance on the company's part they would have tried a lot harder to obfuscate their intentions.
